# Project Rules & Learnings

> The learning journal. Append non-obvious patterns, preferences, and gotchas as they're discovered.
>
> **Keep it high-signal, not append-forever.** Soft cap ~40 lines. When the file grows
> past that, prune: delete things that are no longer true, and promote stabilized
> conventions into `systemPatterns.md` (architecture) or the relevant memory-bank file.
> A line earns its place by helping the next session make a better decision.

## User preferences

- Hooks stay off — Gus runs `/start` manually at session open; don't suggest enabling them
- Check fixes with Codex (ask-codex / codex MCP) before committing

## Code patterns

- Blog posts: MDX in `src/posts/` with `title`/`date`/`excerpt`/`coverImage` frontmatter; hide via `EXCLUDED_POSTS`
- New-post checklist: no `: ` in frontmatter values; do NOT quote the excerpt (listing shows quotes literally); no H1 in the body (page renders the title); cover ≈1600×800 jpeg in `public/images/`

## Gotchas

- Keep `.npmrc` legacy-peer-deps until Next 16 / React 19 peer-dep conflicts resolve — Vercel builds fail without it
- Two frontmatter parsers exist (regex in blog listing, gray-matter in post page) — keep frontmatter simple (no `: ` in values)
- Never run `npm audit fix --force` here — it tries to downgrade next to 9.x; use the scoped postcss override instead
- Verify AI-generated images' real format before committing (`sips -g format` — Gemini saved a PNG with a .jpeg extension; convert with `sips -s format jpeg`)

## Workflow

- Deploy = push to main; Vercel auto-deploys. No tests, no CI in this repo.

